    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Built-in staggered, asymmetrical shelves commonly found in shoin style decoration. This style first because popular at the end of the Muromachi period (1392-1573).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
